				. temporary change to IP task B1
KERNEL_B1_1* $proc
	la, xi	VECTOR_B1(1)
	ii	KERNEL$B1
	$end
				. call before return B1$ takes B1
				. from caller's vector bank
				. so if you nest calls that both
				. change to a service B1
				. you may have to repeat KERNEL$B1
				. but you are not likely to do this


				. call before return B1$ takes B1
				. from caller's vector bank
				. so if you nest calls that both
				. change to a service B1
				. you may have to repeat KERNEL$B1
				. but you are not likely to do this

APP_B1_X* $proc
	ii	B1$		. return to the caller's B1
	$end			. it's the same B1 if the caller was
				. a protocol inline to the IP task

				. otherwise return to the B1 of
				. the separate application task

